LogFile.FinalText: Many homes have pets, and most people prefer dogs or cats. For now, the soft puppy is beating the sweet kitten in the race of being Denmark's most popular pet. While the dog's loyalty explains why it is so popular, many cat owners love the cat's independence. While cat owners think that a dog is too dependant and dirty, many dog owners perceive cats as being lazy and impersonal. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflect their own personality. When a big, strong man buys a big, strong dog, the dog's characteristics enhance the dog owner's ego. On the other hand, a feminine woman often prefer a beautiful and elegant cat. Normally, dogs and cats get along if they are used to each other. Often, the dog owner and the cat owner fight more than the dog and the cat.
